{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895519277,"sessionID":"ses_284611580ffeIf38TurH3phN6H","part":{"id":"prt_d7b9f16b2001HB6WKKwmQHte6p","messageID":"msg_d7b9efcb6001H9rV1zrh1N6dQt","sessionID":"ses_284611580ffeIf38TurH3phN6H","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_b90997f021e64a5e84c38f20","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AgentCube Documentation\n2: \n3: Welcome to the AgentCube documentation repository. This directory contains comprehensive technical documentation for the AgentCube project.\n4: \n5: ## Documentation Structure\n6: \n7: ```\n8: docs/\n9: ├── README.md                          # This file - documentation guide\n10: ├── architecture/                      # Architecture design documentation\n11: │   ├── overview.md                    # System architecture overview\n12: │   ├── components.md                  # Core component designs\n13: │   ├── data-flow.md                   # Data flow and request processing\n14: │   ├── deployment.md                  # Deployment architectures\n15: │   └── security.md                    # Security architecture\n16: ├── api/                               # API documentation\n17: │   ├── README.md                      # API documentation index\n18: │   ├── router.md                      # Router API reference\n19: │   ├── workload-manager.md            # Workload Manager API reference\n20: │   ├── store.md                       # Store API reference\n21: │   ├── sandbox-manager.md             # Sandbox Manager API reference\n22: │   └── picod.md                       # PicoD API reference\n23: ├── design/                            # Design specifications\n24: │   ├── coding-standards.md            # Go coding standards\n25: │   ├── naming-conventions.md          # Naming conventions\n26: │   └── error-handling.md              # Error handling specification\n27: └── docs/                              # Docusaurus site source (AR-042)\n28:     ├── docs/\n29:     │   ├── architecture/              # Rendered architecture docs\n30:     │   ├── api/                       # Rendered API docs\n31:     │   └── design/                    # Rendered design specs\n32:     └── ...\n33: ```\n34: \n35: ## Reader Guide\n36: \n37: ### For Developers\n38: \n39: Start here if you're developing with or contributing to AgentCube:\n40: \n41: 1. **[Architecture Overview](/docs/docs/architecture/overview.md)** - Understand system design\n42: 2. **[API Reference](/docs/docs/api/README.md)** - Learn available APIs\n43: 3. **[Coding Standards](/docs/docs/design/coding-standards.md)** - Follow project conventions\n44: 4. **[Quick Start](/docs/docs/getting-started/quickstart.md)** - Get started quickly\n45: \n46: ### For Architects\n47: \n48: Focus on high-level design and decisions:\n49: \n50: 1. **[Architecture Overview](/docs/docs/architecture/overview.md)** - System vision and layers\n51: 2. **[Component Design](/docs/docs/architecture/components.md)** - Core component responsibilities\n52: 3. **[Data Flow](/docs/docs/architecture/data-flow.md)** - Request processing flows\n53: 4. **[Security Architecture](/docs/docs/architecture/security.md)** - Security model\n54: 5. **[Deployment Architecture](/docs/docs/architecture/deployment.md)** - Deployment patterns\n55: \n56: ### For Operators\n57: \n58: Focus on deployment and operations:\n59: \n60: 1. **[Deployment Architecture](/docs/docs/architecture/deployment.md)** - Deployment modes\n61: 2. **[Kubernetes Deployment](/docs/docs/deployment/kubernetes.md)** - K8s installation\n62: 3. **[Helm Deployment](/docs/docs/deployment/helm.md)** - Helm chart usage\n63: 4. **[Monitoring Guide](/docs/docs/advanced/monitoring.md)** - Observability setup\n64: \n65: ## Documentation Categories\n66: \n67: ### Architecture Documentation (`architecture/`)\n68: \n69: Technical design documents describing system architecture:\n70: \n71: - **overview.md** - System vision, layers, and components\n72: - **components.md** - Detailed component designs\n73: - **data-flow.md** - Request flows and state machines\n74: - **deployment.md** - Deployment architectures (dev, staging, production)\n75: - **security.md** - Security model and measures\n76: \n77: ### API Documentation (`api/`)\n78: \n79: Complete API reference for all components:\n80: \n81: - **router.md** - Session management and routing API\n82: - **workload-manager.md** - Sandbox lifecycle API\n83: - **store.md** - Storage interface and operations\n84: - **sandbox-manager.md** - Sandbox operations and warm pool\n85: - **picod.md** - In-sandbox command execution API\n86: \n87: ### Design Specifications (`design/`)\n88: \n89: Coding standards and design conventions:\n90: \n91: - **coding-standards.md** - Go and Python coding standards\n92: - **naming-conventions.md** - Naming rules for all identifiers\n93: - **error-handling.md** - Error handling patterns and conventions\n94: \n95: ## Relationship with Docusaurus (AR-042)\n96: \n97: This documentation serves as the **source of truth** for the AgentCube project. The content is synchronized with the Docusaurus documentation site (AR-042):\n98: \n99: | Aspect | This Repository (AR-043) | Docusaurus Site (AR-042) |\n100: |--------|-------------------------|-------------------------|\n101: | **Purpose** | Source documentation | Rendered documentation site |\n102: | **Format** | Markdown files | React/Markdown with navigation |\n103: | **Location** | `docs/docs/` | Built and deployed site |\n104: | **Audience** | Developers (direct access) | All users (web interface) |\n105: | **Updates** | Edit markdown files | Automatic on build |\n106: \n107: ### Workflow\n108: \n109: 1. Write/update documentation in `docs/docs/`\n110: 2. Commit changes to repository\n111: 3. CI/CD builds Docusaurus site\n112: 4. Site deployed with updated content\n113: \n114: ## Documentation Standards\n115: \n116: ### File Format\n117: \n118: - All documentation uses Markdown (`.md`)\n119: - Files use UTF-8 encoding\n120: - Line endings are Unix-style (LF)\n121: \n122: ### Front Matter\n123: \n124: All markdown files include Docusaurus front matter:\n125: \n126: ```yaml\n127: ---\n128: id: overview\n129: title: Architecture Overview\n130: slug: /architecture/overview\n131: sidebar_label: Overview\n132: ---\n133: ```\n134: \n135: ### Diagrams\n136: \n137: Use Mermaid for diagrams when possible:\n138: \n139: ````markdown\n140: ```mermaid\n141: graph TD\n142:     A[Client] --> B[Router]\n143:     B --> C[Redis]\n144:     B --> D[Sandbox]\n145: ```\n146: ````\n147: \n148: Or ASCII art for simple diagrams:\n149: \n150: ```\n151: Client → Router → Redis → Sandbox\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ### Code Examples\n155: \n156: Always specify the language for code blocks:\n157: \n158: ````markdown\n159: ```go\n160: package main\n161: \n162: func main() {\n163:     fmt.Println(\"Hello, World!\")\n164: }\n165: ```\n166: ````\n167: \n168: ```python\n169: print(\"Hello, World!\")\n170: ```\n171: \n172: ## Contributing\n173: \n174: ### Updating Documentation\n175: \n176: 1. Edit the appropriate markdown file\n177: 2. Follow existing structure and style\n178: 3. Update front matter if needed\n179: 4. Run `npm run build` in `docs/` to verify\n180: 5. Submit pull request\n181: \n182: ### Adding New Sections\n183: \n184: 1. Create new markdown file in appropriate directory\n185: 2. Add front matter with unique `id` and `slug`\n186: 3. Update `sidebars.ts` to add to navigation\n187: 4. Cross-reference from existing documents\n188: \n189: ### Review Checklist\n190: \n191: - [ ] Spelling and grammar correct\n192: - [ ] Code examples are accurate and tested\n193: - [ ] Diagrams render correctly\n194: - [ ] Links work (internal and external)\n195: - [ ] Follows naming conventions\n196: - [ ] Consistent with existing content\n197: - [ ] Front matter is correct\n198: \n199: ## Tools\n200: \n201: ### Local Development\n202: \n203: ```bash\n204: # Install dependencies\n205: cd docs\n206: npm install\n207: \n208: # Start development server\n209: npm run start\n210: \n211: # Build for production\n212: npm run build\n213: \n214: # Run tests\n215: npm run test\n216: ```\n217: \n218: ### Validation\n219: \n220: ```bash\n221: # Check markdown links\n222: npm run check-links\n223: \n224: # Verify front matter\n225: npm run check-frontmatter\n226: ```\n227: \n228: ## Versioning\n229: \n230: Documentation follows AgentCube versioning:\n231: \n232: - **Main branch** - Latest development version\n233: - **Release branches** - Version-specific documentation (e.g., `release-0.1`)\n234: - **Tags** - Snapshots at release points\n235: \n236: ## Related Documents\n237: \n238: - [Project Overview](../../project.md)\n239: - [Design Specification](../../design.md)\n240: - [Contributing Guide](../../CONTRIBUTING.md)\n241: - [AR-042 Proposal](../../changes/AR-042/proposal.md)\n242: \n243: ## Support\n244: \n245: For documentation issues or questions:\n246: \n247: - **GitHub Issues** - Report documentation bugs\n248: - **Discussions** - Ask questions\n249: - **Slack** - Real-time chat support\n250: \n251: ## License\n252: \n253: Documentation is licensed under the same license as the AgentCube project.\n\n(End of file - total 253 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AgentCube Documentation\n\nWelcome to the AgentCube documentation repository. This directory contains comprehensive technical documentation for the AgentCube project.\n\n## Documentation Structure\n\n```\ndocs/\n├── README.md                          # This file - documentation guide\n├── architecture/                      # Architecture design documentation\n│   ├── overview.md                    # System architecture overview\n│   ├── components.md                  # Core component designs\n│   ├── data-flow.md                   # Data flow and request processing\n│   ├── deployment.md                  # Deployment architectures\n│   └── security.md                    # Security architecture\n├── api/                               # API documentation\n│   ├── README.md                      # API documentation index\n│   ├── router.md                      # Router API reference\n│   ├── workload-manager.md            # Workload Manager API reference\n│   ├── store.md                       # Store API reference","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/README.md","time":{"start":1775895519223,"end":1775895519275}}}}
