{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895551344,"sessionID":"ses_284611580ffeIf38TurH3phN6H","part":{"id":"prt_d7b9f8ba40011Md82aBDzhK6Km","messageID":"msg_d7b9f767b001myozb3G4DBJFDl","sessionID":"ses_284611580ffeIf38TurH3phN6H","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_5dfef31800a345e390d85e7f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/package.json"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/package.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"name\": \"agentcube-docs\",\n3:   \"version\": \"0.0.0\",\n4:   \"private\": true,\n5:   \"scripts\": {\n6:     \"docusaurus\": \"docusaurus\",\n7:     \"start\": \"docusaurus start\",\n8:     \"build\": \"docusaurus build\",\n9:     \"swizzle\": \"docusaurus swizzle\",\n10:     \"deploy\": \"docusaurus deploy\",\n11:     \"clear\": \"docusaurus clear\",\n12:     \"serve\": \"docusaurus serve\",\n13:     \"write-translations\": \"docusaurus write-translations\",\n14:     \"write-heading-ids\": \"docusaurus write-heading-ids\",\n15:     \"typecheck\": \"tsc\",\n16:     \"test\": \"jest --coverage\"\n17:   },\n18:   \"dependencies\": {\n19:     \"@docusaurus/core\": \"^3.10.0\",\n20:     \"@docusaurus/plugin-content-blog\": \"^3.10.0\",\n21:     \"@docusaurus/plugin-content-docs\": \"^3.10.0\",\n22:     \"@docusaurus/plugin-content-pages\": \"^3.10.0\",\n23:     \"@docusaurus/preset-classic\": \"^3.10.0\",\n24:     \"@mdx-js/react\": \"3.0.1\",\n25:     \"clsx\": \"2.1.1\",\n26:     \"prism-react-renderer\": \"2.3.1\",\n27:     \"react\": \"18.3.1\",\n28:     \"react-dom\": \"18.3.1\",\n29:     \"webpack\": \"5.88.0\"\n30:   },\n31:   \"devDependencies\": {\n32:     \"@docusaurus/module-type-aliases\": \"^3.10.0\",\n33:     \"@docusaurus/tsconfig\": \"^3.10.0\",\n34:     \"@docusaurus/types\": \"^3.10.0\",\n35:     \"@testing-library/jest-dom\": \"6.4.6\",\n36:     \"@testing-library/react\": \"15.0.7\",\n37:     \"@types/jest\": \"29.5.12\",\n38:     \"@types/node\": \"20.14.0\",\n39:     \"@types/react\": \"18.3.3\",\n40:     \"jest\": \"29.7.0\",\n41:     \"jest-environment-jsdom\": \"29.7.0\",\n42:     \"ts-jest\": \"29.1.4\",\n43:     \"typescript\": \"5.4.5\"\n44:   },\n45:   \"browserslist\": {\n46:     \"production\": [\n47:       \">0.5%\",\n48:       \"not dead\",\n49:       \"not op_mini all\"\n50:     ],\n51:     \"development\": [\n52:       \"last 3 chrome version\",\n53:       \"last 3 firefox version\",\n54:       \"last 5 safari version\"\n55:     ]\n56:   },\n57:   \"engines\": {\n58:     \"node\": \">=18.0\"\n59:   }\n60: }\n\n(End of file - total 60 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"name\": \"agentcube-docs\",\n  \"version\": \"0.0.0\",\n  \"private\": true,\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"docusaurus\": \"docusaurus\",\n    \"start\": \"docusaurus start\",\n    \"build\": \"docusaurus build\",\n    \"swizzle\": \"docusaurus swizzle\",\n    \"deploy\": \"docusaurus deploy\",\n    \"clear\": \"docusaurus clear\",\n    \"serve\": \"docusaurus serve\",\n    \"write-translations\": \"docusaurus write-translations\",\n    \"write-heading-ids\": \"docusaurus write-heading-ids\",\n    \"typecheck\": \"tsc\",\n    \"test\": \"jest --coverage\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@docusaurus/core\": \"^3.10.0\",\n    \"@docusaurus/plugin-content-blog\": \"^3.10.0\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/package.json","time":{"start":1775895551326,"end":1775895551342}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895551364,"sessionID":"ses_284611580ffeIf38TurH3phN6H","part":{"id":"prt_d7b9f87b100188R8h6mz0jG8Vm","messageID":"msg_d7b9f767b001myozb3G4DBJFDl","sessionID":"ses_284611580ffeIf38TurH3phN6H","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_a5531b87238742c49472e66f","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/security.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/security.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: security\n3: title: Security Architecture\n4: slug: /architecture/security\n5: sidebar_label: Security\n6: ---\n7: \n8: ## Security Overview\n9: \n10: AgentCube implements defense-in-depth security with multiple layers of protection:\n11: \n12: 1. **Authentication** - Verify identity of clients\n13: 2. **Authorization** - Control access to resources\n14: 3. **Isolation** - Prevent cross-sandbox interference\n15: 4. **Encryption** - Protect data in transit\n16: 5. **Auditing** - Track all operations\n17: \n18: ## Authentication\n19: \n20: ### JWT Authentication\n21: \n22: AgentCube supports JWT RS256 token-based authentication:\n23: \n24: ```yaml\n25: auth:\n26:   jwt:\n27:     enabled: true\n28:     publicKey: |\n29:       -----BEGIN PUBLIC KEY-----\n30:       MIIBIjANBgkqhkiG9w0BAQEFAAOCAQ8AMIIBCgKCAQEA...\n31:       -----END PUBLIC KEY-----\n32:     algorithm: RS256\n33:     issuer: agentcube\n34:     audiences:\n35:       - agentcube-api\n36: ```\n37: \n38: ### Kubernetes Token Review\n39: \n40: For Kubernetes-native authentication:\n41: \n42: ```yaml\n43: auth:\n44:   kubernetes:\n45:     enabled: true\n46:     serviceAccount: agentcube-service\n47:     audiences:\n48:       - agentcube-api\n49: ```\n50: \n51: ### Token Format\n52: \n53: ```json\n54: {\n55:   \"sub\": \"user-123\",\n56:   \"iss\": \"agentcube\",\n57:   \"aud\": \"agentcube-api\",\n58:   \"exp\": 1700000000,\n59:   \"iat\": 1699996400,\n60:   \"permissions\": [\"sandbox:create\", \"sandbox:read\", \"sandbox:delete\"]\n61: }\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ## Authorization\n65: \n66: ### RBAC Model\n67: \n68: AgentCube implements Role-Based Access Control:\n69: \n70: | Role | Permissions |\n71: |------|-------------|\n72: | `admin` | Full access to all resources |\n73: | `developer` | Create, read, delete own sandboxes |\n74: | `viewer` | Read-only access |\n75: | `service` | Programmatic access for services |\n76: \n77: ### Kubernetes RBAC\n78: \n79: ```yaml\n80: apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\n81: kind: Role\n82: metadata:\n83:   name: agentcube-sandbox-manager\n84: rules:\n85: - apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n86:   resources: [\"sandboxes\"]\n87:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"delete\"]\n88: - apiGroups: [\"\"]\n89:   resources: [\"pods\", \"services\"]\n90:   verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"create\", \"delete\"]\n91: ```\n92: \n93: ## Network Isolation\n94: \n95: ### Pod Security\n96: \n97: Sandboxes run with restricted security contexts:\n98: \n99: ```yaml\n100: securityContext:\n101:   runAsNonRoot: true\n102:   runAsUser: 1000\n103:   allowPrivilegeEscalation: false\n104:   readOnlyRootFilesystem: true\n105:   capabilities:\n106:     drop:\n107:       - ALL\n108: ```\n109: \n110: ### Network Policies\n111: \n112: ```yaml\n113: apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\n114: kind: NetworkPolicy\n115: metadata:\n116:   name: sandbox-isolation\n117: spec:\n118:   podSelector:\n119:     matchLabels:\n120:       agentcube.volcano.sh/type: sandbox\n121:   policyTypes:\n122:   - Ingress\n123:   - Egress\n124:   ingress:\n125:   - from:\n126:     - podSelector:\n127:         matchLabels:\n128:           agentcube.volcano.sh/type: router\n129:     ports:\n130:     - protocol: TCP\n131:       port: 8080\n132:   egress:\n133:   - to:\n134:     - podSelector:\n135:         matchLabels:\n136:           agentcube.volcano.sh/type: router\n137: ```\n138: \n139: ### Resource Isolation\n140: \n141: Each sandbox has dedicated resource limits:\n142: \n143: ```yaml\n144: resources:\n145:   limits:\n146:     cpu: \"2\"\n147:     memory: \"2Gi\"\n148:     ephemeral-storage: \"5Gi\"\n149:   requests:\n150:     cpu: \"500m\"\n151:     memory: \"512Mi\"\n152: ```\n153: \n154: ## Encryption\n155: \n156: ### TLS Configuration\n157: \n158: All external traffic uses TLS:\n159: \n160: ```yaml\n161: ingress:\n162:   enabled: true\n163:   tls:\n164:   - secretName: agentcube-tls\n165:     hosts:\n166:       - api.agentcube.io\n167: ```\n168: \n169: ### Internal Communication\n170: \n171: Internal service-to-service communication:\n172: \n173: - Router ↔ Workload Manager: mTLS\n174: - Router ↔ Redis: TLS\n175: - Workload Manager ↔ K8s API: TLS\n176: \n177: ## Secrets Management\n178: \n179: ### Kubernetes Secrets\n180: \n181: Sensitive data stored in Kubernetes secrets:\n182: \n183: ```yaml\n184: apiVersion: v1\n185: kind: Secret\n186: metadata:\n187:   name: agentcube-secrets\n188: type: Opaque\n189: stringData:\n190:   jwt-private-key: |\n191:     -----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\n192:     ...\n193:     -----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\n194:   redis-password: supersecret\n195: ```\n196: \n197: ### Secret Rotation\n198: \n199: AgentCube supports automatic secret rotation:\n200: \n201: ```yaml\n202: secrets:\n203:   rotation:\n204:     enabled: true\n205:     interval: 24h\n206:     notifyOnRotation: true\n207: ```\n208: \n209: ## Auditing\n210: \n211: ### Audit Logs\n212: \n213: All operations are logged:\n214: \n215: ```json\n216: {\n217:   \"timestamp\": \"2024-01-15T10:30:00Z\",\n218:   \"actor\": \"user-123\",\n219:   \"action\": \"sandbox:create\",\n220:   \"resource\": \"sandbox-456\",\n221:   \"result\": \"success\",\n222:   \"details\": {\n223:     \"image\": \"python:3.11\",\n224:     \"resources\": {\"cpu\": \"1\", \"memory\": \"512Mi\"}\n225:   }\n226: }\n227: ```\n228: \n229: ### Log Configuration\n230: \n231: ```yaml\n232: audit:\n233:   enabled: true\n234:   output: stdout\n235:   format: json\n236:   includeRequest: true\n237:   includeResponse: false\n238: ```\n239: \n240: ## Security Best Practices\n241: \n242: 1. **Enable authentication** - Never run without auth in production\n243: 2. **Use RBAC** - Grant minimum necessary permissions\n244: 3. **Enable network policies** - Isolate sandbox traffic\n245: 4. **Rotate secrets regularly** - Automate secret rotation\n246: 5. **Monitor audit logs** - Set up alerting for suspicious activity\n247: 6. **Keep updated** - Regularly update AgentCube and dependencies\n\n(End of file - total 247 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: security\ntitle: Security Architecture\nslug: /architecture/security\nsidebar_label: Security\n---\n\n## Security Overview\n\nAgentCube implements defense-in-depth security with multiple layers of protection:\n\n1. **Authentication** - Verify identity of clients\n2. **Authorization** - Control access to resources\n3. **Isolation** - Prevent cross-sandbox interference\n4. **Encryption** - Protect data in transit\n5. **Auditing** - Track all operations\n\n## Authentication\n\n### JWT Authentication","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/architecture/security.md","time":{"start":1775895551319,"end":1775895551361}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895551366,"sessionID":"ses_284611580ffeIf38TurH3phN6H","part":{"id":"prt_d7b9f89c7001FSLQSDkesiQSHv","messageID":"msg_d7b9f767b001myozb3G4DBJFDl","sessionID":"ses_284611580ffeIf38TurH3phN6H","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_4f8ac48563d6441ab6daf0d0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: api-reference\n3: title: API Reference\n4: slug: /api-reference\n5: sidebar_label: API Reference\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # API Documentation\n9: \n10: This section provides comprehensive API documentation for all AgentCube components.\n11: \n12: ## Available APIs\n13: \n14: | API | Description | Status |\n15: |-----|-------------|--------|\n16: | [Router API](/api-reference/router) | Session management and request routing | Stable |\n17: | [Workload Manager API](/api-reference/workload-manager) | Sandbox lifecycle management | Stable |\n18: | [Store API](/api-reference/store) | Session state storage interface | Stable |\n19: | [Sandbox Manager API](/api-reference/sandbox-manager) | Sandbox operations interface | Beta |\n20: | [PicoD API](/api-reference/picod) | In-sandbox command execution | Beta |\n21: \n22: ## API Conventions\n23: \n24: ### Base URLs\n25: \n26: | Environment | URL |\n27: |-------------|-----|\n28: | Development | `http://localhost:8080` |\n29: | Staging | `https://staging-api.agentcube.io` |\n30: | Production | `https://api.agentcube.io` |\n31: \n32: ### Authentication\n33: \n34: All API requests (except health endpoints) require authentication:\n35: \n36: ```http\n37: Authorization: Bearer <jwt_token>\n38: ```\n39: \n40: ### Response Format\n41: \n42: All responses use JSON format:\n43: \n44: ```json\n45: {\n46:   \"data\": { ... },\n47:   \"error\": null\n48: }\n49: ```\n50: \n51: Error responses:\n52: \n53: ```json\n54: {\n55:   \"data\": null,\n56:   \"error\": {\n57:     \"code\": \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\",\n58:     \"message\": \"Session 'sess_123' not found\",\n59:     \"details\": {\n60:       \"sessionId\": \"sess_123\"\n61:     }\n62:   }\n63: }\n64: ```\n65: \n66: ### HTTP Status Codes\n67: \n68: | Code | Meaning |\n69: |------|---------|\n70: | 200 | Success |\n71: | 201 | Created |\n72: | 204 | No Content |\n73: | 400 | Bad Request |\n74: | 401 | Unauthorized |\n75: | 403 | Forbidden |\n76: | 404 | Not Found |\n77: | 409 | Conflict |\n78: | 429 | Too Many Requests |\n79: | 500 | Internal Server Error |\n80: | 503 | Service Unavailable |\n81: \n82: ### Versioning\n83: \n84: API version is included in the path:\n85: \n86: ```\n87: /api/v1/sessions\n88: /api/v1/workloads\n89: ```\n90: \n91: ### Rate Limiting\n92: \n93: Rate limits are enforced per client:\n94: \n95: ```http\n96: X-RateLimit-Limit: 100\n97: X-RateLimit-Remaining: 95\n98: X-RateLimit-Reset: 1700000000\n99: ```\n100: \n101: ## Client Libraries\n102: \n103: | Language | Repository | Status |\n104: |----------|------------|--------|\n105: | Python | `sdk-python/` | Stable |\n106: | Go | `client-go/` | Stable |\n107: | CLI | `cmd/cli/` | Stable |\n108: \n109: ## Related Documents\n110: \n111: - [Architecture Overview](/architecture/overview)\n112: - [Quick Start](/getting-started/quickstart)\n113: - [Authentication Guide](/advanced/authentication)\n\n(End of file - total 113 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: api-reference\ntitle: API Reference\nslug: /api-reference\nsidebar_label: API Reference\n---\n\n# API Documentation\n\nThis section provides comprehensive API documentation for all AgentCube components.\n\n## Available APIs\n\n| API | Description | Status |\n|-----|-------------|--------|\n| [Router API](/api-reference/router) | Session management and request routing | Stable |\n| [Workload Manager API](/api-reference/workload-manager) | Sandbox lifecycle management | Stable |\n| [Store API](/api-reference/store) | Session state storage interface | Stable |\n| [Sandbox Manager API](/api-reference/sandbox-manager) | Sandbox operations interface | Beta |\n| [PicoD API](/api-reference/picod) | In-sandbox command execution | Beta |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/api/README.md","time":{"start":1775895551323,"end":1775895551365}}}}
