{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895581540,"sessionID":"ses_284611580ffeIf38TurH3phN6H","part":{"id":"prt_d7b9fffee001zZh9P9SmHGYRxM","messageID":"msg_d7b9fef5f0011qY6IOoi569rnU","sessionID":"ses_284611580ffeIf38TurH3phN6H","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_7856db65e3c8456aa6c7c1a3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/coding-standards.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/coding-standards.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: coding-standards\n3: title: Coding Standards\n4: slug: /design/coding-standards\n5: sidebar_label: Coding Standards\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Coding Standards\n9: \n10: This document defines the coding standards for the AgentCube project.\n11: \n12: ## Go Code Standards\n13: \n14: ### Code Formatting\n15: \n16: All Go code must be formatted using standard tools:\n17: \n18: ```bash\n19: # Format code\n20: gofmt -w .\n21: \n22: # Or with imports optimization\n23: goimports -w .\n24: ```\n25: \n26: **Formatting Rules:**\n27: \n28: | Rule | Standard |\n29: |------|----------|\n30: | Line width | 120 characters maximum |\n31: | Indentation | Tabs (not spaces) |\n32: | Braces | K&R style (opening brace on same line) |\n33: | Blank lines | Separate logical blocks |\n34: \n35: **Example:**\n36: \n37: ```go\n38: package router\n39: \n40: import (\n41:     \"context\"\n42:     \"time\"\n43:     \n44:     \"github.com/gin-gonic/gin\"\n45: )\n46: \n47: // Router handles request routing\n48: type Router struct {\n49:     config *Config\n50:     store  store.Store\n51: }\n52: \n53: // NewRouter creates a new Router instance\n54: func NewRouter(config *Config, store store.Store) *Router {\n55:     return &Router{\n56:         config: config,\n57:         store:  store,\n58:     }\n59: }\n60: ```\n61: \n62: ### Naming Conventions\n63: \n64: #### Package Names\n65: \n66: - Use lowercase, no underscores\n67: - Keep names short and descriptive\n68: - Avoid common library names\n69: \n70: ```go\n71: // Good\n72: package router\n73: package workloadmanager\n74: package sandbox\n75: \n76: // Bad\n77: package Router\n78: package workload_manager\n79: package pkg\n80: ```\n81: \n82: #### exported Identifiers\n83: \n84: - Exported: Capital first letter\n85: - Private: Lowercase first letter\n86: \n87: ```go\n88: // Exported\n89: type Router struct{}\n90: func NewRouter() *Router{}\n91: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"not found\")\n92: \n93: // Private\n94: type routerConfig struct{}\n95: func (r *Router) setupRoutes() {}\n96: const maxRetries = 3\n97: ```\n98: \n99: #### Constants\n100: \n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 354. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: coding-standards\ntitle: Coding Standards\nslug: /design/coding-standards\nsidebar_label: Coding Standards\n---\n\n# Coding Standards\n\nThis document defines the coding standards for the AgentCube project.\n\n## Go Code Standards\n\n### Code Formatting\n\nAll Go code must be formatted using standard tools:\n\n```bash\n# Format code\ngofmt -w .","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/coding-standards.md","time":{"start":1775895581522,"end":1775895581539}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895581542,"sessionID":"ses_284611580ffeIf38TurH3phN6H","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba00643001z85Bi68HJrzXWW","messageID":"msg_d7b9fef5f0011qY6IOoi569rnU","sessionID":"ses_284611580ffeIf38TurH3phN6H","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_9a877ca7d5b04fc79886dbdd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/naming-conventions.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/naming-conventions.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: naming-conventions\n3: title: Naming Conventions\n4: slug: /design/naming-conventions\n5: sidebar_label: Naming Conventions\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Naming Conventions\n9: \n10: This document defines naming conventions for the AgentCube project.\n11: \n12: ## CRD Naming\n13: \n14: ### Resource Names\n15: \n16: Use plural, lowercase, kebab-case for CRD names:\n17: \n18: ```yaml\n19: # Good\n20: agentruntimes\n21: codeinterpreters\n22: sandboxes\n23: sessions\n24: \n25: # Bad\n26: AgentRuntimes\n27: agent_runtime\n28: sandboxList\n29: ```\n30: \n31: ### Short Names\n32: \n33: Define short names for common resources:\n34: \n35: ```yaml\n36: apiVersion: apiextensions.k8s.io/v1\n37: kind: CustomResourceDefinition\n38: metadata:\n39:   name: agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n40: spec:\n41:   names:\n42:     kind: AgentRuntime\n43:     plural: agentruntimes\n44:     singular: agentruntime\n45:     shortNames:\n46:     - ar\n47: ```\n48: \n49: | Resource | Short Name |\n50: |----------|------------|\n51: | `agentruntimes` | `ar` |\n52: | `codeinterpreters` | `ci` |\n53: | `sandboxes` | `sb` |\n54: | `sessions` | `sess` |\n55: \n56: ## API Group\n57: \n58: ### Format\n59: \n60: ```\n61: <resource>.agentcube.volcano.sh\n62: ```\n63: \n64: **Examples:**\n65: \n66: ```\n67: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\n68: scheduling.agentcube.volcano.sh\n69: ```\n70: \n71: ### Versions\n72: \n73: Use standard Kubernetes API versioning:\n74: \n75: ```\n76: v1alpha1  # Alpha (breaking changes expected)\n77: v1beta1   # Beta (minor changes expected)\n78: v1        # Stable (no breaking changes)\n79: ```\n80: \n81: **Example:**\n82: \n83: ```yaml\n84: apiVersion: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\n85: kind: AgentRuntime\n86: ```\n87: \n88: ## Kubernetes Resources\n89: \n90: ### Deployments\n91: \n92: ```yaml\n93: # Format: agentcube-{component}\n94: metadata:\n95:   name: agentcube-router\n96:   name: agentcube-workload-manager\n97:   name: agentcube-agentd\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ### Services\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 329. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: naming-conventions\ntitle: Naming Conventions\nslug: /design/naming-conventions\nsidebar_label: Naming Conventions\n---\n\n# Naming Conventions\n\nThis document defines naming conventions for the AgentCube project.\n\n## CRD Naming\n\n### Resource Names\n\nUse plural, lowercase, kebab-case for CRD names:\n\n```yaml\n# Good\nagentruntimes","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/naming-conventions.md","time":{"start":1775895581524,"end":1775895581540}}}}
