{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775895595238,"sessionID":"ses_284611580ffeIf38TurH3phN6H","part":{"id":"prt_d7ba033e1001ohKTCym4s2FfhT","messageID":"msg_d7ba013ad001QqlJlqLijhwtMu","sessionID":"ses_284611580ffeIf38TurH3phN6H","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_bed0ce829c964bceb334a287","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/error-handling.md","limit":100},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/error-handling.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: id: error-handling\n3: title: Error Handling\n4: slug: /design/error-handling\n5: sidebar_label: Error Handling\n6: ---\n7: \n8: # Error Handling\n9: \n10: This document defines error handling patterns and conventions for the AgentCube project.\n11: \n12: ## Error Types\n13: \n14: ### Application Errors\n15: \n16: ```go\n17: package router\n18: \n19: // Error codes\n20: const (\n21:     ErrCodeSessionNotFound     = \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n22:     ErrCodeSessionExists       = \"SESSION_EXISTS\"\n23:     ErrCodeSandboxNotReady     = \"SANDBOX_NOT_READY\"\n24:     ErrCodeRateLimitExceeded   = \"RATE_LIMIT_EXCEEDED\"\n25:     ErrCodeUnauthorized        = \"UNAUTHORIZED\"\n26:     ErrCodeInvalidInput        = \"INVALID_INPUT\"\n27:     ErrCodeInternalError       = \"INTERNAL_ERROR\"\n28: )\n29: \n30: // Error variables\n31: var (\n32:     ErrSessionNotFound     = errors.New(\"router: session not found\")\n33:     ErrSessionExists       = errors.New(\"router: session already exists\")\n34:     ErrSandboxNotReady     = errors.New(\"router: sandbox not ready\")\n35:     ErrRateLimitExceeded   = errors.New(\"router: rate limit exceeded\")\n36:     ErrUnauthorized        = errors.New(\"router: unauthorized\")\n37:     ErrInvalidInput        = errors.New(\"router: invalid input\")\n38:     ErrInternalError       = errors.New(\"router: internal error\")\n39: )\n40: ```\n41: \n42: ### Error Struct\n43: \n44: For structured error responses:\n45: \n46: ```go\n47: type Error struct {\n48:     // Code is the error code\n49:     Code string `json:\"code\"`\n50:     \n51:     // Message is the human-readable message\n52:     Message string `json:\"message\"`\n53:     \n54:     // Details contains additional context\n55:     Details map[string]interface{} `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n56:     \n57:     // Cause is the underlying error\n58:     Cause error `json:\"-\"`\n59: }\n60: \n61: func (e *Error) Error() string {\n62:     if e.Cause != nil {\n63:         return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %v\", e.Message, e.Cause)\n64:     }\n65:     return e.Message\n66: }\n67: \n68: func (e *Error) Unwrap() error {\n69:     return e.Cause\n70: }\n71: ```\n72: \n73: ## Error Creation\n74: \n75: ### Simple Errors\n76: \n77: ```go\n78: // Use errors.New for static errors\n79: var ErrNotFound = errors.New(\"store: not found\")\n80: ```\n81: \n82: ### Formatted Errors\n83: \n84: ```go\n85: // Use fmt.Errorf for dynamic errors\n86: func (s *Store) Get(key string) ([]byte, error) {\n87:     if key == \"\" {\n88:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"key cannot be empty\")\n89:     }\n90:     // ...\n91: }\n92: ```\n93: \n94: ### Wrapped Errors\n95: \n96: ```go\n97: // Use errors.Wrap for context\n98: func CreateSandbox(ctx context.Context, spec *SandboxSpec) (*Sandbox, error) {\n99:     if err := validate(spec); err != nil {\n100:         return nil, errors.Wrap(err, \"validate sandbox spec\")\n\n(Showing lines 1-100 of 376. Use offset=101 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\nid: error-handling\ntitle: Error Handling\nslug: /design/error-handling\nsidebar_label: Error Handling\n---\n\n# Error Handling\n\nThis document defines error handling patterns and conventions for the AgentCube project.\n\n## Error Types\n\n### Application Errors\n\n```go\npackage router\n\n// Error codes\nconst (","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/docs/docs/design/error-handling.md","time":{"start":1775895595187,"end":1775895595235}}}}
